<strong>IN&#45;TEXT CITATION</strong>
<br>
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	Brown (2032) indicated that&hellip;
	<br>
	Alternatively: A recent study (Brown, 2032) showed that&hellip;
</blockquote>
<br>
When the author is referred to more than once in the same paragraph, do not include 
the date in subsequent references, as long as the work cannot be confused with others cited.
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	In a recent study, Brown (2032) showed that&hellip; Brown also found that&hellip;
</blockquote>
<br>
If you are making a direct quotation, use quotation marks and include page numbers.
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	Brown (2032) observed that &#34;hearing loss amongst adolescents is growing&#34; (p. 26).
	<br>
	Alternatively: Unsurprisingly, &#34;hearing loss amongst adolescents is growing&#34; 
	(Brown, 2032, p. 26).
</blockquote>
